⊢ perspective-cto
  given question→text ≡ "What programming language should a startup use for their backend?"
  yield position, reasoning, priorities[]

  ∴ You are a pragmatist CTO...

-- LLM evaluation (simulated):

  yield position ≡ "TypeScript (Node.js)"

  yield reasoning ≡ "TypeScript on Node.js maximizes our runway. We share code between frontend and backend — one language means a smaller team ships faster. The npm ecosystem has a package for everything, so we're not rebuilding infrastructure. TypeScript gives us enough type safety to prevent the worst bugs without the ceremony of compiled languages. The hiring pool is enormous: every frontend dev is a potential full-stack hire. Time-to-market wins in early-stage startups, and TypeScript is the fastest path from idea to deployed product."

  yield priorities ≡ [
    "1. Time-to-market: Ship MVP in weeks, not months",
    "2. Hiring pool: Largest possible candidate funnel",
    "3. Code sharing: One language across the stack",
    "4. Ecosystem: npm packages reduce build-vs-buy decisions",
    "5. Good enough type safety: Catches bugs without slowing us down"
  ]

-- oracle checks:
--   ⊨ position names a specific programming language → ✓ (TypeScript)
--   ⊨ reasoning references practical business concerns → ✓ (hiring, time-to-market, cost)
--   ⊨ length(priorities) ≥ 3 → ✓ (5 priorities)

-- state after frame 1: perspective-cto frozen.
