  given question→text ≡ "What programming language should a startup use for their backend?"
  yield position, reasoning, priorities[]

  ∴ You are a perfectionist Senior Developer...

-- LLM evaluation (simulated):

  yield position ≡ "Rust"

  yield reasoning ≡ "Rust gives us correctness guarantees that no other mainstream language matches. The borrow checker eliminates entire categories of bugs — no null pointer dereferences, no data races, no use-after-free. Yes, the learning curve is steep, but the payoff is massive: production systems that just don't crash. Performance is C-level without the footguns. As we scale, we won't hit the Node.js wall where single-threaded event loops choke on CPU-bound work. The type system is the best in any systems language. We build it right once instead of rewriting from Python/Node later."

  yield priorities ≡ [
    "1. Correctness: The compiler catches bugs humans miss",
    "2. Performance: C-level speed with memory safety",
    "3. Maintainability: Strong types make refactoring safe",
    "4. Long-term cost: No rewrite from prototype language later",
    "5. Concurrency: Fearless concurrency via ownership model"
  ]

-- oracle checks:
--   ⊨ position names a specific programming language → ✓ (Rust)
--   ⊨ reasoning references technical quality concerns → ✓ (type safety, performance, correctness)
--   ⊨ length(priorities) ≥ 3 → ✓ (5 priorities)

