  yield position ≡ "TypeScript (Node.js)"

  yield reasoning ≡ "I'm looking at the burn rate. TypeScript developers are abundant and cheaper than Rust specialists. A full-stack TypeScript team of 3 can do the work of 5 split across languages. Node.js hosting is cheap — serverless on AWS Lambda or Vercel costs pennies at startup scale. The ecosystem means less custom code, fewer engineer-months, faster revenue. I've seen too many startups die because they over-engineered in a 'better' language and ran out of runway before product-market fit. Ship fast, validate, then optimize. You can always rewrite the hot paths later."

  yield priorities ≡ [
    "1. Burn rate: Minimize cost per feature shipped",
    "2. Talent cost: Abundant developers keep salaries competitive",
    "3. Speed to revenue: Fastest path to paying customers",
    "4. Infrastructure cost: Cheap hosting at startup scale",
    "5. Optionality: Easy to hire, easy to pivot, easy to sell"
  ]

